name: Parade of The END
description:
Come! And come to the parade!
the death has welcomed us! the end has begun!
Come! and come to the crowds!
as we march on toward the infinite of the end!
Come and come!
we never sleep
the memories will never fade
we are never hungry
Come! and Come!
your sanity! your sanity! your sanity!

============================================================

This one is inspired by (I'm sorry) the victim of schizophrenia and the way anxiety affects the way of our mind, affecting either the bad way or the good way, how is this correlated? So there a chanting and many shadowy people it represents the voice inside our heads, about the eyes, it represents the anxiety of the person because the eyes keep moving on the left to right
and the person in middle is the actual person, us, you, me, everyone.
